{"id":"323997963_Tensions_in_specifying_computing_curricula_for_K-12_Towards_a_principled_approach_for_objectives","abstract":"In this article we examine key issues and tensions for developing and specifying Computing-related elements of curricula design, particularly the role of Computer Science in the curriculum. The article is based on a series of discussions and analyses of curriculum design across various countries with different approaches and traditions of Computing in the curriculum.","authors":["Mary Webb","Timothy C. Bell","Niki Davis","Yaacov J Katz"],"meta":["April 2018it - Information Technology 60(2):59-68","DOI:10.1515/itit-2017-0017","Project: Digitale Bildung"],"references":["305140678_A_K-6_Computational_Thinking_Curriculum_Framework_Implications_for_Teacher_Knowledge","305140594_Arguing_for_Computer_Science_in_the_School_Curriculum","305084487_Programming_in_Slovak_Primary_Schools","343364402_Running_on_Empty_the_Failure_to_Teach_K--12_Computer_Science_in_the_Digital_Age","320283497_Author_Correction_Digital_Citizenship_you_Can't_Go_Home_Again","315938536_The_Forthcoming_Artificial_Intelligence_AI_Revolution_Its_Impact_on_Society_and_Firms","315173769_The_End_of_Moore's_Law_A_New_Beginning_for_Information_Technology","312101153_What_it_means_to_be_a_citizen_in_the_internet_age_Development_of_a_reliable_and_valid_digital_citizenship_scale","311473376_Unlocking_the_clubhouse_women_in_computing","309659300_Surrendering_to_growth_The_European_Union's_goals_for_research_and_technology_in_the_Horizon_2020_framework"]}